# API & Form Rules

## API Route Structure
All API routes must follow:
```ts
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server'

export async function POST(req: NextRequest) {
  try {
    const body = await req.json()
    
    // 1. Validate input
    if (!body.required_field) {
      return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Deskripsi error' }, { status: 400 })
    }
    
    // 2. Business logic
    
    // 3. Return success
    return NextResponse.json({ success: true })
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('API error:', error)
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Gagal memproses permintaan' }, { status: 500 })
  }
}
```

## Contact Form — Required Fields
```ts
{
  name: string      // min 2 char
  company?: string  // optional
  email: string     // valid email format
  phone: string     // Indonesian format
  service: string   // from predefined list
  message: string   // min 20 char
}
```

## Resend Email Pattern
```ts
import { Resend } from 'resend'
const resend = new Resend(process.env.RESEND_API_KEY)

// Notification email to Navale
await resend.emails.send({
  from: 'Website Navale <noreply@domain.com>',
  to: ['cv.navalemitratama@gmail.com'],
  replyTo: senderEmail,
  subject: `[Website] Subjek Email`,
  html: `HTML_TEMPLATE`,
})

// Auto-reply to sender
await resend.emails.send({
  from: 'CV Navale Mitratama <noreply@domain.com>',
  to: [senderEmail],
  subject: 'Konfirmasi — CV Navale Mitratama',
  html: `AUTO_REPLY_TEMPLATE`,
})
```

## Email Template Style
HTML email templates must use:
- Background: `#0B1824` (navy-900) for header
- Accent: `#1A56A0` (blue-brand)
- WhatsApp link: `#25D366`
- Inline styles only (email clients strip `<style>` tags)
- No external fonts in emails

## React Hook Form Pattern
```tsx
'use client'
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form'

type FormData = { field: string }

const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm<FormData>()

// Input with validation
<input
  {...register('field', { required: 'Pesan error Indonesia' })}
  className={`... ${errors.field ? 'border-red-400' : 'border-neutral-300'}`}
/>
{errors.field && <p className="text-red-500 text-xs mt-1">{errors.field.message}</p>}
```

## Form States
Forms must handle all 4 states visually:
- `idle` — default form UI
- `loading` — spinner + disabled button
- `success` — success message + reset option
- `error` — error banner + fallback WA/email link

## Never
- ❌ Use `<form>` HTML element directly — always wrap with react-hook-form
- ❌ Hardcode API key — always use `process.env.RESEND_API_KEY`
- ❌ Send sensitive data (NPWP, etc.) through client-side code
- ❌ Return sensitive error details to client (use generic messages)
